	<title>Length of an Arrow: Examples</title>
	<caption>Length of an Arrow: Examples</caption>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the length of the arrow joining the point <latex>P(4,-1,11)</latex> to the point <latex>Q(-2,6,4)</latex> in <latex>\RNr[3]</latex>.  
			</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>The length of the arrow <latex>\Arrow{P}{Q}</latex> is the distance from <latex>P</latex> to <latex>Q</latex>:</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\aligned
\Length{\Arrow{P}{Q}}\ &=\ \Dstnc{P}{Q} \\
					& =\ \sqrt{(-2-4)^2+(6-(-1))^2+(4-11)^2} \\
					& =\ \sqrt{36+49+49} \\
					& =\ \sqrt{134}
					\endaligned
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</answer>
	</showme>
	
	<showme>
		<statement>
			<para>Find the length of the arrow joining the point <latex>A(1,3,0,5)</latex> to the point <latex>B(2,1,-2,4)</latex> in <latex>\RNr[4]</latex>.  
			</para>
		</statement>
		<answer type="Solution">
			<para>The length of the arrow <latex>\Arrow{A}{B}</latex> is the distance from <latex>A</latex> to <latex>B</latex>:</para>
			<math.display>
				<latex>
					<![CDATA[
					\aligned
\Length{\Arrow{A}{B}}\ &=\ \Dstnc{A}{B} \\
					& =\ \sqrt{(2-1)^2 + (1-3)^2 + ((-2)-0)^2 + (4-5)^2 } \\
					& =\ \sqrt{1 + 4 + 4 + 1} \\
					& =\ \sqrt{10}
					\endaligned
					]]>
				</latex>
			</math.display>
		</answer>
	</showme>
</showme.pack>